        "timestamp": "2018-02-26 12:45:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n\nSomething seems wrong with the size of the commit (all lines seem to be changed). Giving it -2 for now till I check...",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "ab6c4cb161e5077c3316272f9c5d82fd30049346",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2197,
          "name": "Sastry Isukapalli",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sastry@research.att.com",
          "username": "sisukapalli"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-26 13:51:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSeems like Ankit's file was DOS encoded and yours is UNIX so each line is different. I did a dos2unix on Ankit's file and then did a diff, and the diff showed about eight to nine lines.\n\nFirst, I suggest moving the file to UNIX format, so please keep your format. On gerrit, the diff page has a settings option for \"ignore white space\" with a value for \"ignore at line end\". Suggest using that. Other option is the unix \"diff -w\". \n\nNow, there are some issues: original document has \"M\" and \"O\" with the cell header as \"Qualifier\" (mandatory/optional). It should be replaced with the header as \"Required\" and have \"Y\" and \"N\".\n\nSo, Maopeng, would you please make those changes to all tables in the document as well and submit another patchset? Then, after I get a \"+1\" from Ankit or Shankar, I will do the merge.\n\nMore background for context:\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/17645/differences-between-unix-and-windows-files\n\nUNIX uses a single Line Feed (LF) to signify a new line, Windows uses a Carriage Return/Line Feed (CRLF).",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
